            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWhen%20God%20makes%20a%20covenant%2C%20He%20means%20eternal%20business.%20In%20biblical%20times%2C%20a%20covenant%20was%20sealed%20between%20two%20parties%20by%20their%20cutting%20an%20animal%20in%20half%20and%20walking%20between%20the%20pieces%20in%20a%20figure-eight%20movement.%20Israel%20had%20entered%20into%20that%20kind%20of%20covenant%20with%20God%2C%20yet%20failed%20to%20keep%20it.%20God%20was%20forced%20to%20respond%20with%20these%20words%3A%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22Because%20you%20have%20refused%20the%20terms%20of%20our%20covenant%2C%20I%20will%20cut%20you%20apart%20just%20as%20you%20cut%20apart%20the%20calf%20when%20you%20walked%20between%20its%20halves%20to%20solemnize%20your%20vows%22%20(Jeremiah%2034%3A18).%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIt%20is%20human%20nature%20to%20make%20and%20then%20break%20covenants.%20God%2C%20however%2C%20cannot%20break%20a%20covenant.%20He%20promised%20Jeremiah%20that%20if%20he%20could%20break%20God's%20%22covenant%20with%20the%20day%20and%20the%20night%20so%20that%20they%20do%20not%20come%20on%20their%20usual%20schedule%2C%20only%20then%20will%20my%20covenant%20with%20David%2C%20my%20servant%2C%20be%20broken.%20Only%20then%20will%20he%20no%20longer%20have%20a%20descendant%20to%20reign%20on%20his%20throne%22%20(Jeremiah%2033%3A20-21).%20The%20chances%20of%20David%20not%20having%20an%20heir%20as%20king%20on%20Israel's%20throne%20are%20less%20than%20the%20chances%20of%20the%20sun%20not%20shining%20anymore!%20That's%20how%20faithful%20God%20is!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWith%20a%20God%20who%20is%20that%20unchangeable%20and%20faithful%2C%20we%20must%20also%20be%20true%20to%20Him-the%20faithful%20God%20who%20keeps%20His%20covenant%20forever.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
